<p>
A topic that we often get asked about is the quantity &amp; quality of non-native currencies, also known as <b>IOUs</b> moving across the XRP Ledger. The XRPL supports sending and receiving any quantifiable asset (fiat currencies such as USD &amp; EUR, crypto-currencies such as BTC &amp; ETH, physical assets such as gold &amp; silver, and pretty much anything else) across the network so long as there is an institution known as a <b>gateway</b> or a <b>custodian</b> backing that asset. It is the responsibility of the custodian to manage the real world assets which back the on-ledger IOUs and to provide the services used to issue and redeem those tokens, exchanging the digital value for physical.
</p>

