<ul>
  <li>
    Backed or unbacked <b>transactions look exactly the same</b> on the XRPL. If the BTC being transferred is backed by actual Bitcoin or it is not, the XRPL transaction would manifest in the exact same manner. It is important to not lose sight of the forest for the trees.
  </li>

  <li>
    Finally until proven otherwise, we shouldn't assume that transactions are not legitimate. Why not give the network the benefit of the doubt.
  </li>
</ul>

